parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ETM can cause the vehicle to surge or hesitate, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle surges or hesitates
the ETS light and Check Engine light illuminate
the vehicle goes into "limp-home" mode
the vehicle stalls or loses power
and the throttle body needs to be cleaned or replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or hesitates
the ETS light and Check Engine light illuminate
the vehicle goes into "limp-home" mode
and the throttle body needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The misfiring of the ignition coil can cause the vehicle to hesitate or stall, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or stalls
the Check Engine light illuminates
and the ignition coil needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to hesitate or stall, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or stalls
the transmission slips or fails to engage
and the transmission needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ETS can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power while driving, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The ETS light comes on
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the engine surges or bucks
the cruise control disengages
and the vehicle may enter a "cripple mode" at any given point.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the immobilizer and antenna ring can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, which can leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle will not start
the ignition key will not turn
the vehicle will stall while driving
and the immobilizer light may come on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical failures can cause various systems to malfunction, including the engine, brakes, and dashboard electronics, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The dashboard lights may not work
the engine may stall
the brakes may not function properly
and the windshield wipers may not work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Electronic Throttle System (ETS) can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or hesitate, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The ETS light illuminates on the dashboard
the vehicle loses power
stalls
or hesitates
the accelerator pedal becomes unresponsive
and the vehicle may experience sudden deceleration or jerking motions.
